headline: Public Storage (NYSE:PSA) Declares Regular Dividend Amid 10% Price Decline Last Quarter
summary: Public Storage (NYSE:PSA) recently affirmed a regular dividend and provided subdued corporate guidance, including expected revenue growth between 1.3% decline to a 0.8% increase, reflecting anticipated challenges. Despite these steady signals, the company's share price fell by nearly 10% over the last quarter. This decline aligns with broader market turbulence, where indices such as the S&P 500 have also experienced significant drops amid heightened volatility from trade tensions. Although...
